Description:
Waeg, an IBM Company is a Salesforce Platinum Partner providing certified consultancy for enterprise-level organizations across Europe.




We are looking for a QA Engineer who will be responsible for implementing technical testing in support of the strategic development of customised solutions built on Salesforce.




By leveraging the latest SFDC technology, you will help our clients surf the wave of digital transformation.




YOUR ROLE




As a QA Engineer, you will:

Review quality specifications and technical design documents to provide timely and meaningful feedback;
Create detailed, comprehensive, and well-structured test plans and test cases;
Estimate, prioritize, plan and coordinate quality testing activities;
Design and implement tests, debug and define corrective actions;
Review system requirements;
Participate in product design reviews to provide input on functional requirements, product designs, schedules, or potential problems;
Track quality assurance metrics.




With strong technical and communication skills, the QA Engineer is responsible for conducting tests before product launches to ensure software runs smoothly and meets client needs while being cost-effective.




YOUR SKILLS




In order to be successful in our team, we expect:

Ability to analyse and evaluate projects to determine best test approach/methodology;
Capacity to understand stakeholder needs and requirements to ensure the delivery of quality results;
Capacity to stimulate and support an environment of collaboration, sharing of information, ideas and resources;
Easiness with changing work plans to manage shifting priorities.




You also have good interpersonal skills and communication skills, verbal and written to both technical and non-technical audiences that are in a geographically dispersed environment.




You are able to speak and write English fluently, and you can produce high-quality technical documentation and analysis.




You can work independently and in a fast-paced environment with tight deadlines and minimal supervision, on multiple tasks and deliver quality products.




YOUR BENEFITS




At Waeg, an IBM Company, you’ll have the opportunity to work with amazing global brands in complex and challenging projects, which will provide you with many personal growth possibilities.




You will be part of a global team, with a can-do and supportive attitude where innovation and collaborative thinking are encouraged.




We will offer you a competitive salary and we will support your continuous growth path with our own Waeg academy and 12 days of training a year.




Locations




You can join one of our Offices in Amsterdam, Brussels, Copenhagen, Dublin, Lisbon, Paris, or Warsaw or even work remotely from any city in Europe!
